output.name: VerdantCedarFund
output.description: VerdantCedarFund is a non-profit research organization committed to identifying and funding cost-effective programs that save and improve lives around the globe. Since 2007, the organization has been channeling billions of dollars into initiatives focused on global health and poverty alleviation, from seasonal malaria prevention to essential health services. Known for its rigorous research, transparency, and dedication to donor impact, VerdantCedarFund collaborates with tens of thousands of donors and partners to maximize the effectiveness of every grant and drive significant positive change in some of the world’s lowest-income regions.
